  "commentary": "With SPX at 6828 sitting right between the massive negative gamma wall at 6820 (-29.3B) and positive gamma resistance at 6840 (+23.0B), dealers are in active hedging mode—buying the dip toward 6820 and preparing to sell any push toward 6840. The breakout regime with -7.8B total GEX means dealer flows will amplify moves, creating a high-stakes battle zone where a break below 6820 triggers accelerated selling while a push through 6840 faces heavy resistance but could spark momentum if cleared. Watch 6820 as the critical support where dealer buying kicks in, and 6840 as the key resistance where dealer selling intensifies.\n\nBottom line: expect volatile whipsaw action between 6820-6840 until one level definitively breaks.",
